[5] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

2 Jan 2015 Germany: Rapid detection test
http://www.dw.de/rapid-ebola-detection-certainty-in-minutes/av-18167029

[Researchers in Germany have developed a new test that identifies a protein unique to the Ebola virus from a patient's throat swab within minutes. To carry out the test you do not need any specially qualified staff or a laboratory with expensive equipment. An important advance. I wonder whether a multiplex assay could be designed to detect Marburg and Lassa viruses at the same time. - Mod.LK]

[But untested in the field against control positive and negative sera to check for false positives and false negatives. - Mod.JW]

